<html><head><title>EverQuest Book Now Available!</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>EverQuest Book Now Available!</h3><p>Remember that <a href="http://vault.ign.com/View.php?view=editorials.detail&id=230" target="_new">EverQuest piece</a> we did earlier this year for the game's 10th Anniversary? Well if you recall correctly, Sony had mentioned they were working on a hardcover book detailing the ten year quest the game has undergone.<br><br>That book is <a href="https://store.station.sony.com/hardgood.jsp?SKU=EQ1RE-HG-BK0609-EQ10TH" target="_new">finally available</a>! It retails for $34.99.<br><br>The hardcover volume includes:<br><blockquote><li>The story behind the creation of EverQuest and EverQuest II</li><br><li>Interviews with key contributors to the EverQuest legacy, including John Smedley, Russell Shanks, Brad McQuaid and others</li><br><li>Fantastic artwork illustrating every page, including reproductions of EverQuest and EverQuest II box covers and highly detailed art pieces from Legends of Norrath</li><br><li>Concept art and promotional images of famous EverQuest and EverQuest II characters and locations</li><br><li>Descriptions and commentary from the development teams behind the EverQuest franchise</li></blockquote> So go check it out, looks like a great collector's item.<br><br></div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Monday, 17 Aug, 2009<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=53960">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=53960</a><br>Printed On: Tue Apr 17 7:04:21 PDT 2012<br>©2008 IGN Entertainment</font></span>